what_failed: Regression (0.93x): Isolated dimension table filters into separate CTEs (date_dim and item) before joining with the fact table (store_sales). This allows DuckDB to build small hash tables from highly selective dimension filters first, then perform efficient hash joins against the large fact table.
why_it_failed: Pre-filtered and joined store_sales to date CTE BEFORE the 3-way fact table join (store_sales <- store_returns <- catalog_sales). By materializing the date-filtered store_sales early, the optimizer loses the ability to push filters across the multi-way fact join and reorder joins optimally.
